<br>
I agree that it's like salt in the wound to release a very problematic upgrade and then turn around and offer seeminly preferential treatment to those who pay an extra 30 dollars a month.  It just goes back to the concept that those who have the money and spend more of it have the bigger voice.  The mass majority has very little.  We should be glad that we have what we have. The massive popularity of this game is what created this concept.  If 100 or even 1000 people walk away from this game because of the Luclin upgrade, i doubt that Verant will even flinch.<br>
<br>
